4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE ELECTRONIC
5 TRANSMISSION OF A BALLOT BY A DISABLED VOTER; ALLOWING A DISABLED ELECTOR TO RETURN
6 A VOTED BALLOT USING AN ENCRYPTED ELECTRONIC TRANSMISSION SYSTEM APPROVED BY THE
7 SECRETARY OF STATE UNDER CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES; REQUIRING THE SECRETARY OF STATE
8 TO ADOPT ENCRYPTION AND SECURITY STANDARDS FOR AN ELECTRONIC TRANSMISSION
9 SYSTEM; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING
10 SECTION 13-13-246, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 Section 1. Section 13-13-246, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "13-13-246. Electronic ballots for disabled persons -- procedures -- definition -- rulemaking. (1)
16 (a) Upon a written or an in-person request from a legally registered or provisionally registered elector with a
17 disability, an election administrator shall provide the elector with an electronic ballot.
18 (b) The request may be made by electronic mail.
19 (2) (a) After receiving a request and verifying that the elector is legally registered or provisionally
20 registered, the election administrator shall provide to the elector an electronic ballot, instructions for completing
21 the ballot, a secrecy envelope or page secrecy cover sheet, and a transmittal cover sheet that includes an
22 elector affirmation. If the elector is provisionally registered, the election administrator shall include instructions
23 about what information the elector shall include with the voted ballot pursuant to 13-13-201(4).
24 (b) The election administrator shall maintain an official log of all ballots provided pursuant to this
25 section.
26 (c) After voting the ballot, the elector shall print the ballot, place it in the secrecy envelope or under
27 the secrecy page, sign the affirmation, including by fingerprint, mark, or agent pursuant to 13-1-116, or provide
28 a driver's license number or the last four digits of the elector's social security number. If the elector returns the
